ATTENTION!  This game has none and will NOT be getting any English Support.  I cannot recommend only for that reason but my review is a thumbs up because the game was a Visual Novel with a very cool design.  It has very great character design and art.  I really love how the style is Water Color even though it is Digital Art.  Lastly the thumbs up because the game isn't very difficult to play.  The generic minigames have a Skip Function and the none generic ones don't have a skip function but are brain dead easy thank goodness.  The questions or the Tarot/Fortune Cards don't seem to matter very much (IT actually probably does for 5 achievements that i do not have PROBABLY).  The H-Scenes have little bit of VA and a bit of animation.  Nonetheless if you must have the CG for your H-Library collection by all means and pick it up on a sale

For anyone that's never played "Lost: Find" from the same Publisher as this group....you will find the game interface to be totally unique and you won't know what you're doing seriously.  The game may or may not give you issues, but I've yet to have anything too major for me to write down a "cons or bugs list".  The game doesn't have much of a tutorial in the beginning so if you do pick this up, you will be going in blind and hopefully you are a quick learner.
press S D G at the same time while at the starting menu. gonna be lot more fun
